This solution works by continuously dividing `n` by 3 until it can no longer be evenly divided. If `n` is a power of 3, this process will eventually result in `n` becoming 1. If `n` is not a power of 3, the process will end with a non-1 value of `n`.

However, this solution uses a loop, which does not satisfy the follow-up question of avoiding loops/recursion. 

